The paper deals with gesture recognition in videos using deep neural nets, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of autoencoder and predictor architectures, as well as an adaptive weighting scheme, suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions improving robustness to lighting conditions, which is a common concern in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of neural nets for gesture recognition suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
